      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas L. Friedman writes, ''I don't much care how the U.N. works as a bureaucracy; I care about how often it can be enlisted to support, endorse and amplify U.S. power.''</p>
        <p>The past genocide of Muslims in Bosnia and the genocide today in Sudan suggest that the United Nations must operate more effectively as a bureaucracy.</p>
        <p>Endorsing and amplifying American power should not be the exclusive goal of the United States. John R. Bolton may not be the best candidate to achieve renewal of the United Nations, but renewal should be sought.</p>
        <p>Rob Brueckner  Bridgewater, N.J., April 27, 2005</p>
      </block>
